    </exercise><exercise id="fs-id2666191" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id3116303">    <para id="import-auto-id3062563">Air temperature in the Sahara Desert can reach
<m:math>
 
  <m:mtext>56.0ºC</m:mtext>
 
</m:math>
 (about
<m:math>
 
  <m:mtext>134ºF</m:mtext>
 
</m:math>). What is the speed of sound in air at that temperature?</para></problem></exercise>
        <exercise id="fs-id2032287" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id3055563">    <para id="import-auto-id1361482">Dolphins make sounds in air and water. What is the ratio of the wavelength of a sound in air to its wavelength in seawater? Assume air temperature is
<m:math>
 
  <m:mtext>20.0ºC</m:mtext>
 
</m:math>.</para></problem>
            <solution id="fs-id1448362" type="problems-exercises">
